FBIS3-11955 "drlat060_b_94007" FBIS-LAT-94-060 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Mar 1994 Caribbean Affairs Haiti Malval Reacts to Threats Against Ministers FL2803183994 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1130 GMT 25 Mar 94 FL2803183994 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio Language: French Article Type:BFN [Text] Resigning Prime Minister Robert's reaction has not been long in coming. In a press release, resigning Prime Minister Robert Malval says he listened with indignation to Mr. Emmanuel Constant's [leader of the Revolutionary Front for the Promotion and Progress of Haiti] threats during a news conference held on 24 March. Constant warned the ministers of Malval's government. They have been summoned not to go to their offices as of Monday, 28 March. The prime minister advised that Constant would be held personally responsible for any attacks in which a member of the government might be the victim, with all the legal consequences. On that score, the the press release signed by interim Prime Minister Robert Malval concludes by saying the prime sent a letter to the public order officials.
